li.p: Animated SVGs (SMIL/CSS-only, no JS) → many work on GitHub. Put the .svg in your repo and embed it like an image:

li.p: Note: JavaScript in SVG is stripped; keep it pure SVG animation.
APNGs (animated PNG) → often render fine, but GIFs are safer cross-browser.
Video autoplay, iframes, or scripts – blocked for security.
CSS/JS animations in the README page itself – external CSS/JS isn’t allowed.
Keep files small (ideally <2–3 MB) so your profile loads fast.
Loop smoothly and use a low frame rate for GIFs to cut size.
If you want “dynamic” animations (e.g., the popular contribution-snake), use a GitHub Action to generate an animated SVG/GIF and commit it, then reference that file in your README.
